Key Match Events: Giannis Antetokounmpo had 41 points and 14 rebounds
Damian Lillard added 29 points for the Bucks, including a couple of free throws with 9.3 seconds left for the game's final points
Post-Match Reflections: The Bucks moved into a virtual tie with the Magic for fourth place in the East with their third straight win
After going 19-15 in Banchero's 10-week absence, the Magic are still missing Jalen Suggs and Franz and Mo Wagner. But the injuries and poor shooting are costing them close games against good teams.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Bucks shot 52% to offset nine missed free throws (seven by Antetokounmpo)
Others: Paolo Banchero returned from an injury and played for the first time since Oct. 30, scoring 34 points and making 5 of 8 3-point shots.
